LAGOS  – The National Directorate of Employment (NDE), has commenced its skill acquisition training in Sustainable Agricultural Development Training Scheme (SADTS) for 133 beneficiaries in Lagos. The directorate also disbursed loans to 38 people in order to help them grow their businesses. The beneficiaries of the loans had benefited from earlier training orgnised by the directorate in the state. Mallam Nuhu Fikpo, the Director-General of NDE, disclosed that SADTS is a programme under the Rural Employment Promotion programme of the NDE and was designed to create sustainable employment tor the unemployed, retirees and others. Fikpo, who was represented at the event by the Lagos State coordinator of NDE, Mrs. Serena Olayebi Edward, explained that the training and loan disbursement were in line with the Federal Government’s policy to curb unemployment, create wealth and generate employment in the country. He disclosed that 133 beneficiaries would be trained under the SADTS programme while 38 beneficiaries, who graduated from the Graduate Agricultural Employment Scheme (GAES), Community-Based Agricultural Employment Scheme (CBAES), Sustainable Agricultural Development Employment Scheme (SADTS) Agricultural Enhancement Scheme (AES) would be been given loans to establish their businesses or grow existing ones. POLL He emphasised the importance of agriculture in the development of the nation’s economy, especially farming, in the area of economic diversification. He said that participants in the SADTS would undergo a three-month theoretical and practical training in sustainable agricultural practices. The Director General urged the beneficiaries and participants to take the training seriously and grasp all aspects of the training in order to optimize the opportunity made available to them and imbibe the culture of continuous improvement and learning.